 dass Arbeit in der digitalen Ökonomie soziale Teilhabe und mehr als die bloße Existenzsicherung garantiert.  aIn the next decades the working world will change fundamentally. What powers affect the labor market? What changes are to be expected? And what does that mean for those involved in labor politics? This conclusive report by the Commission "Work in the Future" - with members from the fields of science, businesses and unions as well as practitioners - presents a diagnosis of the current situation and provides a perspective of the future of work. Particularly, however, the commission offers food for thought on the question how society can master the fast changes so that work in the digital economy guarantees the participation in society and more than mere livelihood.  afunded by Hans-Böckler-Stiftung  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 3.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/3.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aHours of labor. 0aLabor market. 0aLabor policy. 0aQuality of work life. 4aArbeit der Zukunft. 4aArbeits- und Industriesoziologie. 4aArbeitsbeziehungen. 4aArbeitsökonomie. 4aDigitalisierung. 4aGewerkschaften. 4aPolitik. 4aPolitikwissenschaft. 4aSozialpolitik. 4aSoziologie. 4aTransformation. 4aTransformationspakt. 4aZukunft. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh  aDigitalization.  aFuture of Work.  aFuture.  aLabour Economics.  aPolitical Science.  aPolitics.  aSocial Policy.  aSociology of Work and Industry.  aSociology.  aTrade Unions.  aTransformation Agreement.  aTransformation.  aWork Relations.1 aHoffmann, Reiner, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aSchildmann, Christina, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.